'''When a function calls itself, it is called recursion.
Programmming technique allows function to solve a problem by breaking it down into smaller
sub problems of same type.
Each recrusive cell should bring function  closer to a base case, 
which is a condition that stops the recursion.
'''

def factorial(n):
    if n==1:
        return 1
    else:
        return n*factorial(n-1) #recursive cell

x=factorial(5)
print(x)